    • Constructor Detail

      • QuadricSurface

        public QuadricSurface(java.lang.String f,
                      javafx.geometry.Point3D LL,
                      javafx.geometry.Point3D UL,
                      javafx.geometry.Point3D OS)
        Quadric function with upper and lower limits
        Parameters:
        f - String - Quadric function of the form

        J=A*(x^2)+B*(y^2)+C*(z^2) +D*x*y+E*x*z+F*y*z+G*x+H*y+I*z

        can take into account parentheses when squaring the A,B,and C terms
        LL - Point3D - lower limit that will render/interact
        UL - Point3D - upper limit that will render/interact
        OS - Point3D - offset value

      • get_t

        public double get_t(javafx.geometry.Point3D xyz,
                    javafx.geometry.Point3D ijk)
        Uses the quadratic formula combined with the general form of the quadric formula to solve for t in the equation |EndPos| = |StartPos|+t*|v|
        Parameters:
        xyz - Point3D - the start position for the ray
        ijk - Point3D - the vector of the ray
        Returns:
        t double - the value that the vector must be multiplied by in order to reach the intercept position
